'''Sultan Hussain Al-Brake''' ({{Langx|ar|سلطان البريكي}}; born 7 April 1996) is a Qatari professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left-back]] for Qatari club [[Al-Duhail SC|Al-Duhail]] and the [[Qatar national football team|Qatar national team]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mundial11.com/register|title=مونديال 11 - Mundial 11 - إحصائيات - نتائج - أرقام - أخبار - هيد تو هيد|website=www.mundial11.com}}</ref>

Al-Brake was part of the Qatar squad that won the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Our final list for Asia 🏆|url=https://twitter.com/QFA_EN/status/1742493635214454878|publisher=Qatar Football Association|website=Twitter|date=3 January 2024|access-date=3 January 2024}}</ref>

==Club career==
Al-Brake began his professional career with [[Al-Wakrah SC|Al-Wakrah]] in 2015. He was loaned out to Spanish club [[Cultural y Deportiva Leonesa|Cultural Leonesa]] in November 2015 and to Al-Duhail in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|last1=León |first1=Diario de |url=http://www.diariodeleon.es/noticias/deportes/cataries-vuelven-contar_1025972.html|title=Los cataríes vuelven a contar|work=Diario de León |language=Spanish|date=24 November 2015|accessdate=29 August 2017}}</ref> In 2018 he joined Al-Duhail.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.worldfootball.net/person/pe401971/sultan-al-brake/ | title=Sultan Al Brake | date= | access-date=2023-08-14}}</ref>

==International career==
At the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]], Al-Brake was a member of Qatar's squad which won the tournament on home soil. He made two appearances at the tournament, starting their third group match against [[China national football team|China]] and coming off the bench in extra time of Qatar's quarter-final against [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan]], where he scored a penalty in the shootout.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Qatar 1-0 China (Jan 22, 2024) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/668943/china-qatar |access-date=2025-12-03 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Qatar 3-2 Uzbekistan (15 Nov, 2024) Final Score - ESPN (AU) |url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/match/_/gameId/710473/uzbekistan-qatar |access-date=2025-12-03 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref>

At the [[2025 FIFA Arab Cup]], Al-Brake started in Qatar's opening match against [[Palestine national football team|Palestine]], where he scored an own-goal in the 95th minute to lose 1–0.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-12-01 |title=Arab Cup opens in Doha as Palestine claim win against hosts |url=http://www.euronews.com/2025/12/01/arab-cup-kicks-off-in-doha-after-dazzling-opening-ceremony-as-palestine-beat-hosts-qatar |access-date=2025-12-03 |website=euronews |language=en}}</ref>

